d.", "readOnly": true, "type": "string" }, "deliveryControl": { "readOnly": true, "$ref": "DeliveryControl", "description": "Output only. Specifies the pacing set by the publisher." }, "privateAuctionTerms": { "$ref": "PrivateAuctionTerms", "description": "The terms for private auction deals." }, "targeting": { "$ref": "MarketplaceTargeting", "description": "Specifies the subset of inventory targeted by the deal. Can be updated by the buyer before the deal is finalized." }, "buyer": { "readOnly": true, "type": "string", "description": "Output only. Refers to a buyer in The Realtime-bidding API. Format: `buyers/{buyerAccountId}`" }, "billedBuyer": { "readOnly": true, "type": "string", "description": "Output only. When the client field is populated, this field refers to the buyer who creates and manages the client buyer and gets billed on behalf of the client buyer; when the buyer field is populated, this field is the same value as buyer. Format : `buyers/{buyerAccountId}`" }, "client": { "description": "Output only. Refers to a Client. Format: `buyers/{buyerAccountId}/clients/{clientAccountid}`", "type": "string", "readOnly": true }, "name": { "description": "Immutable. The unique identifier of the deal. Auto-generated by the server when a deal is created. Format: buyers/{accountId}/proposals/{proposalId}/deals/{dealId}", "type": "string" }, "sellerTimeZone": { "$ref": "TimeZone", "description": "Output only. Time zone of the seller used to mark the boundaries of a day for daypart targeting and CPD billing.", "readOnly": true }, "flightStartTime": { "type": "string", "format": "google-datetime", "description": "Proposed flight start time of the deal. This will generally be stored in the granularity of one second since deal serving starts at seconds boundary. Any time specified with more granularity (for example, in milliseconds) will be truncated towards the start of time in seconds." }, "programmaticGuaranteedTerms": { "description": "The terms for programmatic guaranteed deals.", "$ref": "ProgrammaticGuaranteedTerms" }, "dealType": { "enumDescriptions": [ "Default, unspecified deal type.", "Preferred deals.", "Private auction deals.", "Programmatic guaranteed deals." ], "enum": [ "DEAL_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED", "PREFERRED_DEAL", "PRIVATE_AUCTION", "PROGRAMMATIC_GUARANTEED" ], "readOnly": true, "description": "Output only. Type of deal.", "type": "string" }, "displayName": { "readOnly": true, "type": "string", "description": "Output only. The name of the deal. Maximum length of 255 unicode characters is allowed. Control characters are not allowed. Buyers cannot update this field. Note: Not to be confused with name, which is a unique identifier of the deal." }, "preferredDealTerms": { "$ref": "PreferredDealTerms", "description": "The terms for preferred deals." }, "description": { "type": "string", "description": "Output only. Free text description for the deal terms.", "readOnly": true }, "flightEndTime": { "description": "Proposed flight end time of the deal. This will generally be stored in a granularity of a second. A value is not necessary for Private Auction deals.", "type": "string", "format": "google-datetime" }, "creativeRequirements": { "readOnly": true, "description": "Output only. Metadata about the creatives of this deal.", "$ref": "CreativeRequirements" }, "proposalRevision": { "format": "int64", "readOnly": true, "description": "Output only. The revision number for the proposal and is the same value as proposal.proposal_revision. Each update to deal causes the proposal revision number to auto-increment. The buyer keeps track of the last revision number they know of and pass it in when making an update. If the head revision number on the server has since incremented, then an ABORTED error is returned during the update operation to let the buyer know that a subsequent update was made.", "type": "string" } }, "type": "object", "id": "Deal", "description": "A deal represents a segment of inventory for displaying ads that co